  "text": "After each experiment, all mussels within the chamber were collected and measured for shell length. Fifteen mussels of varying length were lyophilized for 48 h and measurements of shell length (L) and shell-free biomass (m) were fitted to the standard allometric equation m 5 a 3 L b , where m was expressed in units of milligrams dry weight (mg DW), L was expressed in units of millimeters (mm), and a and b were 0.0018 and 3.11, respectively (r 2 5 0.955). This relationship was then applied to all shell length measurements to calculate total mussel biomass for each chamber experiment. Estimates of mussel tissue biomass were also calculated using Nalepa et al.'s (2014) empirical relationship of m 5 0.00225 3 L 2.968 (r 2 5 0.85, n 5 244), where m was expressed as ashfree dry weight (AFDW). After converting AFDW to DW (1 g DW 5 0.88 g AFDW because the combusted sample ash weight is subtracted from the dry weight to obtain AFDW; [CITATION_1] , the two calculations of mussel biomass differed by < 3%.",
